@page "/terms"

<PageTitle>Terms of Service - Catalyst Software Solutions</PageTitle>

<div class="terms-container">
    <section class="terms-hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
            <p class="lead">Please read these terms carefully</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="terms-content">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
            <div class="last-updated">
                <strong>Last Updated:</strong> @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")
            </div>

            <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
            <p>By accessing and using the Catalyst Software Solutions website and services, you accept and agree to be bound by the terms and provisions of this agreement.</p>

            <h2>2. Services</h2>
            <p>Catalyst Software Solutions provides custom software development, legacy system modernization, cloud solutions, and related technology consulting services. Specific terms for each engagement will be outlined in separate service agreements.</p>

            <h2>3. Consultation Requests</h2>
            <p>When you request a consultation:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>You agree to provide accurate and complete information</li>
                <li>No contractual obligation exists until a formal service agreement is signed</li>
                <li>Consultations are provided for informational purposes only</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p>All content on this website, including but not limited to text, graphics, logos, and software, is the property of Catalyst Software Solutions and is protected by copyright and trademark laws.</p>

            <h2>5. Client Responsibilities</h2>
            <p>When engaging our services, clients agree to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Provide timely feedback and necessary information</li>
                <li>Maintain confidentiality of any credentials or access provided</li>
                <li>Comply with payment terms outlined in service agreements</li>
                <li>Use delivered software in accordance with agreed-upon terms</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>6. Warranties and Disclaimers</h2>
            <p>While we strive for excellence, our services are provided "as is" unless otherwise specified in a service agreement. Specific warranties and guarantees will be outlined in individual contracts.</p>

            <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p>Catalyst Software Solutions shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from the use of our services or website.</p>

            <h2>8. Confidentiality</h2>
            <p>We respect the confidentiality of client information and projects. Specific confidentiality terms will be outlined in non-disclosure agreements and service contracts.</p>

            <h2>9. Payment Terms</h2>
            <p>Payment terms for services will be specified in individual service agreements. Generally:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Invoices are due within 30 days unless otherwise specified</li>
                <li>Late payments may incur additional fees</li>
                <li>Milestone-based payments may be required for larger projects</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>10. Termination</h2>
            <p>Either party may terminate a service agreement according to the terms specified in that agreement. Termination conditions and obligations will be clearly outlined in service contracts.</p>

            <h2>11. Changes to Terms</h2>
            <p>We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Continued use of our services after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the modified terms.</p>

